cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image landmark detection using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new loss function for validating the accuracy of landmark estimation, which involves training the network to estimate the accuracy of its own predictions, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). The paper also introduces a novel batch balancing approach, which involves weighting the importance of samples based on their produced loss, indicating a focus on optimization and statistical methods (cs.MM).
